Kesha Voice Kit — vendored vosk-tts runtime subset
====================================================

This crate is a trimmed copy of the runtime portions of
`andreytkachenko/vosk-tts-rs` v0.1.0
(https://github.com/andreytkachenko/vosk-tts-rs), licensed under
Apache License 2.0. See `LICENSE` in this directory.

Original authors: andrey@iadev.ru, Alpha Cephei Inc.

We vendor only what `Synth::synth_audio` transitively needs:

- `model.rs`  — model + dictionary + config loader (download/path-discovery
                paths removed; callers always pass an explicit directory).
- `synth.rs`  — phoneme assembly + ONNX inference.
- `g2p.rs`    — Russian rule-based grapheme-to-phoneme (unchanged).
- `tokenizer.rs` — small inline BERT WordPiece tokenizer (NEW; replaces
                `tokenizers` crate to drop onig_sys / esaxx-rs / bzip2 /
                lzma / zstd transitives that broke Windows MSVC linkage).

Dropped from upstream (not needed for the kesha-engine runtime path):

- gRPC server/client (`tonic`, `prost`, `tokio`, `axum`, `hyper`, `tower`)
- HTTP model download (`reqwest`, `zip`)
- `tokenizers` crate (replaced with inline WordPiece — see Apache 2.0
   parity-test commentary in `src/tokenizer.rs`).
- `dirs`, `clap`, `log`, `env_logger`, `num_cpus`, `rayon`, `hound`
   (the WAV writer; kesha re-uses its own `tts::wav::encode_wav`).
- The `bin/` entrypoints (CLI + server + client).

Modifications: see git history under `rust/vendor/vosk-tts/`.
